Last weekend, three generations of the Beck family set out to harvest disease-free oysters from managed reserves in the Chesapeake Bay.
Bill Beck, a waterman for 21 years, expressed concern over the declining oyster population.
Environmental groups, frustrated with slow progress, are taking legal action against the EPA.
Nutria, a destructive pest, have been successfully cleared from thousands of acres in Maryland.
Efforts to introduce Asian oysters into the bay face criticism and concerns over potential irreversible consequences.
Despite challenges, traditional oyster festivals and events continue to celebrate the bay's rich heritage and ongoing restoration efforts.
